Kaleb Greiner is back to work on the plan for GQ Jr. as the deer has been very frequent on the Cuddeback cameras. In the process, Kaleb goes over his strategies for summer trail camera placement and how it helps him come hunting season. Finally, the Midwest Whitetail team has some awesome news as we welcome Drake Lamb back to the team. We're super excited and we hope everyone enjoys the video. Thanks for the support!

programme.title: Chasing A Giant Droptine Buck In Iowa, Choosing The Best Tree Stand Locations

With it being year two, Kaleb talks about what he learned last season, how it is influencing stand locations for this fall, and how he hopes it will help Steve catch up to the giant drop tine buck that's been showing up on camera. Finally, we jump over to Area 52 with Zach Rozmus who sets the stage for two new stand locations for this coming fall.

programme.title: 3 Killer Spots For A Giant Buck, Bow Hunting Adjustments Based On Past Success
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we kick things off with Lee Abraham in southern Iowa as he breaks down his plan for his top target buck, a giant known as GQ Jr. Looking back on the historic chase that saw him wrap his tag on a giant 204" buck known as GQ, Lee breaks down what he's learned from those hunts and makes adjustments for this season. Those adjustments come in the form of 3 different killer stand locations that he hopes will find him wrapping a tag around another giant this season. Following this, we jump over to catch up with Andy Melton and David Williams who give us an update on their '23 deer season plans and a brief how-to on growing your own oak trees at home! Finally, we jump to the west to the plains of Kansas with Mike Reed who gives us a sneak peek at what's to come in next week's show. Stick around and catch an awesome property that could be yours listed by our partners at UC Hunting Properties.
